headline: Ford already breaks a promise it made to investors last week
summary: The top brass at Ford Motor Co. has been saying the same thing for over a year: The company is well on its way to fixing its quality issues. In 2023, Ford spent $4.8 billion fixing customer vehicles, a 15% increase from the previous year. It set aside $1,203 for warranty repairs on each car it sold ...
